Both CAD- and textview have view history implemented: FORWARD and BACK
buttons are in use when several files have been opened one after one.
For example, touching a BACK button of a CAD-view on the left above the
3D model changes something else which was shown earlier. The size of
history is unlimited for textview, but CAD-view is able to rememder
only three previous vies. If you open more, the oldest one ceases to
exist.<br>
<br>
The LISTING button of CAD-view reveales a menu where perspective view
or orthogonal X-, Y- or Z-view can be chosen. That menu also lists all
the parts making the 3D model on the view and every part can be
individually hide and show. If the 3D model is dynamic &#8211; meaning it has
movements &#8211; you can touch PLAY button. <br>
<br>
The PARAGRAPHS button of textview reveales another menu where you see
all the paragraphs of the current text. By touching a paragraph on a
menu textview moves to that position .<br>
<br>
If you flip your device, Tasavalta-application shows two views side by
side:<br>
